IN THE UNITED STATES CIRCUIT COURT FOR THE DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF JOHN W. CONSIDINE, for writ of habeas corpus.
No. 626 STIPULATION.
It is hereby stipulated and agreed by and between the State of Washington, acting by and through the State of Honorable Patrick Henry Winston, Attorney general of the State of Washington, and Harrison Bostwick, Attorney for petitioner, John W. Considine, that all procedings in the foregoing entitled cause be, and the same are hereby dismissed; and
It is hereby further stipulated and agreed that the Court may make and enter an oder of dismissal herein, upon application of either party hereto, witout further notice, without costs to either party.
Dated, Seattle, Washington, December 11th, 1897.
Patrick H Winston Attorney general of the State of Washington.
Harrison Bostwick Attorney for Petitioner.
